  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Response to Super Typhoon Mangkhut</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">(1)  Vulnerable families will be able to use the cash assistance to buy their immediate needs and augment the loss of income since they were not able to harvest their crops.  (2)  Local groups will be supported by partner organisers to strengthen their resources and capacities to understand the risks in they face and plan their action to minimise or address those risks.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Phase 1 will address life-saving needs while Phase 2 will focus on assets recovery through collective action.
Phase 1 addresses the immediate needs of vulnerable families especially their loss of income and difficulty to access cash while Phase 2 addresses building community resilience by giving them the space to plan and implement how they will do this.  We will build our evidence of how communities, through organised groups will be able to recover and strengthen their capacities to cope with risks in their environment.  Our goal is to have local actors and communities design their humanitarian responses when they experience disasters.</narrative>
  </description>
